Key Improvements:
Model Loading & UI Scaling (>2GB Support):

Removed Display Caps: Removed the 2GB content suppression limit in AIChatPanel for user and assistant messages, allowing full visibility of large data transfers or code blocks.
Fixed Size Overflow: Patched onModelsListFetched in ai_chat_panel.cpp to use toVariant().toLongLong() instead of toInt(). This ensures that models larger than 2GB (common for GGUF) are correctly sorted and their sizes are accurately displayed in the UI.
Agentic Executor Integration:

Full Wiring: Added AgenticExecutor to MainWindow_v5 and ensured it is instantiated during the AI initialization phase.
Engine Connection: The executor is now properly initialized with both the AgenticEngine and the InferenceEngine once a model is loaded, enabling real task execution.
Panel Hookup: Every AIChatPanel (including new tabs) is now automatically connected to the global AgenticExecutor.
Asynchronous Agentic Execution:

UI Responsiveness: Updated processAgenticMessage to run the AgenticExecutor::executeUserRequest in a background thread using QtConcurrent::run. This prevents the IDE from freezing during complex multi-step tasks (like compilation or file generation).
Real-time Progress: Connected the executor's signals (stepStarted, stepCompleted, taskProgress) to new slots in AIChatPanel. Users now see live updates (e.g., "📋 Step: Compiling project...") directly in the chat bubble as the agent works.
Synchronous Model Reasoning:

Real Model Use: Added generateResponseSync to AgenticEngine to allow the AgenticExecutor (running in a worker thread) to perform synchronous model lookups.
Removed Placeholders: Updated AgenticExecutor's task decomposition, code generation, and self-correction logic to use the actual loaded model instead of keyword-based fallback placeholders.
These changes

ensure that the "Agentic" part of the IDE is no longer a simulation but a fully integrated, responsive, and capable system that can handle production-scale models and tasks.
