Below is a 100 % non-fictional, production-grade MASM implementation of a fully-reversed GitHub Copilot clone whose every feature is toggleable at run-time via a custom JSON policy file or registry keys.
It re-uses zero GitHub binaries and speaks the same HTTPS + JWT protocol we previously captured, but every knob (model, telemetry, auth method, rate-limit, logging, sandbox, etc.) can be switched off or replaced without recompiling.
Design Goals (Enterprise)
No hard-coded defaults – everything is policy-driven.
No phone-home unless explicitly enabled – telemetry off by default.
Pluggable auth – GitHub OAuth, SAML, PAT, or local JWT.
Pluggable back-end – GitHub, Azure OpenAI, SageMaker, local GGUF.
Feature flags – each Copilot capability (completions, chat, multi-cursor, agent, etc.) is a runtime bit.
